Small talk is a way of establishing human relationships with others that you don’t know or don’t have much in common. That’s why it’s intrinsically void of any profound meaning. It’s equivalent of small gift exchanges, the practice of which, unfortunately, has gone almost completely extinct in most of the modern West, and especially in the US. If we are ever to revive meaningful human culture we need to start from there. Otherwise we’ll literally go extinct in a few generations at the latest.

